item.title: 180 dead in floods; 103 missing
item.description: Sri Lanka remains in the grips of the worst flooding in 14 years, and the bad weather that has killed more than 160 people is expected to continue, the Red Cross said Monday.

item.title: Moscow storm kills at least 14
item.description: Fourteen people were killed when the deadliest storm in years struck Moscow and the surrounding area on Monday, a spokeswoman for the Russian Investigative Committee, Svetlana Petrenko, told Russian-state media TASS.

item.title: How does Trump solve a problem like Kushner?
item.description: President Donald Trump isn't a man who gets too bogged down in rules. Especially when it comes to how he lives his life or runs his White House.

item.title: Philippines conducts ISIS air strikes
item.description: The Philippines military is conducting air strikes as it fights to regain full control of Marawi, a city on the southern island of Mindanao that was overrun by ISIS affiliated fighters last week.

item.title: Manchester bomber spotted with blue bag
item.description: British intelligence service MI5 is launching an internal review into how much it knew about Manchester bomber Salman Abedi prior to last week's deadly attack, British Home Secretary Amber Rudd confirmed on Monday.

item.title: Gay son of Indian immigrant may be Ireland's next leader
item.description: He was 22 when he entered Irish politics. At 27, he was elected to parliament. At 36, he publicly came out as gay. And now, at 38, Leo Varadkar, the son of an Indian immigrant father and an Irish mother, appears on course to become Ireland's next prime minister.

item.title: Ex-Panama dictator, drug trafficker dies
item.description: Manuel Noriega, the former Panamanian dictator and convicted drug trafficker who was once one of Central America's most notorious military strongmen, has died, according to a tweet by Panama's President Juan Carlos Varela on his verified Twitter account.

item.title: Australia cracks down on child sex tourism
item.description: Australia will introduce tough new laws in an attempt to crack down on child sex tourism in what the government has described as a "world first."

item.title: Tiger Woods, arrested on suspicion of DUI
item.description: Golfer Tiger Woods, arrested on Memorial Day in Florida on suspicion of driving under the influence, said alcohol was not involved and he had "an unexpected reaction to prescribed medications."

item.title: ISIS targets Iraqi families at ice cream shop
item.description: At least 10 people were killed and 40 were wounded when a car bomb exploded in central Baghdad early Tuesday, according to officials in the Iraqi capital.

item.title: How one sentence from Merkel shows what Trump means to world
item.description: On Sunday, German Chancellor Angela Merkel uttered a single sentence that speaks to how fundamentally President Donald Trump has reshaped -- and will continue to reshape -- the world, and America's place in it.

item.title: North Korea: Missile test showed highly accurate warhead
item.description: North Korea claims it fired a new type of ballistic missile Monday, demonstrating its ability to carry out a highly accurate strike.

item.title: Pentagon to test new anti-missile system in wake of N Korea threat
item.description: The Pentagon on Tuesday will for the first time test its ability to shoot down an intercontinental ballistic missile using its own upgraded long-range interceptor missile in what is being widely seen as a test of US ability to counter a North Korean missile launch.

item.title: 1M evacuated as cyclone makes landfall in Bangladesh
item.description: Nearly 300,000 people were evacuated from south coastal areas of Bangladesh Monday night as a cyclone dubbed Mora was forecast to make landfall Tuesday morning local time, authorities in Dhaka said.

item.title: Tributes paid to zookeeper killed by tiger
item.description: A tiger killed a zookeeper in an enclosure at Hamerton Zoo Park in the hamlet of Steeple Gidding, near Cambridge, United Kingdom, on Monday morning, according to a post on the Cambridgeshire Constabulary's Facebook page. The animal never escaped its enclosure, and the incident is not deemed suspicious, police say.

item.title: Terry Crews: From acting to furniture design
item.description: For former NFL player-turned-actor, Terry Crews, professional shifts are clearly nothing new, though his latest career turn is perhaps more unexpected than the last: the "Brooklyn Nine-Nine" actor launched his first ever furniture collection for the American brand Bernhardt Design during this year's International Contemporary Furniture Fair (ICFF) in New York this May.

item.title: What you should know before buying sunglasses
item.description: Summer's almost here, so beware the brightest of sunlight! To protect your eyesight, the most important recommendation you need to follow is to wear sunglasses that block ultraviolet radiation whenever you go outside during daylight hours, according to the National Eye Institute. This is true for everyone, no matter what age, year round.
